snippet.textDisplay:
In the very early hours of this morning, on its 5 minute news flashes broadcasted at the top of the hour, National Public Radio (NPR) WAS CLAIMING THAT ONE MILLION PEOPLE HAVE NOW DIED FROM THE CORONAVIRUS!!! Their staff is so poorly educated and so intent on creating as much hysteria as possible that they didn't even think how the number could have jumped from less than 50,000 yesterday to 1 million overnight. Can you have a stupider crew. Later they re-edited the 6:00 A.M., 7:00 AM and 8:00 AM news briefs that are left on the NPR 5-minute website, but you can hear now what is the news anchor starting to read in midair and not the usual way their clips begin. News flashes for earlier hours were not revised so they still talk about one million deaths. One million may be the figure of people infected worldwide, but NPR anchors clearly said one million deaths!

Also until a few days ago NPR was vehemently attacking and mocking President Trump and outlets like Fox for even talking about chloroquine and hydroxychloroquine as drugs that could be used for coronavirus. Then this week they pretended as if they never made that outright rejection and shifted their attack to the hoarding of those drugs preventing people who are dependent on them for other conditions from being able to obtain them.

Every day NPR keeps making a story attacking Trump for one thing or another on how he's handling the crisis primarily painting a picture of utter ignorance, confusion, and incompetence. But now and then it has stories defending China against being faulted for its part in the origin and spread of coronavirus. Imagine: NPR leaps to defend China as it mercilessly attacks Trump. This is what NPR has been all about for several years now. You can't get more biased and partisan than the undereducated and hate filled crowd at NPR.

snippet.textDisplay: I agree with your brother Chris.. Kudos to you!!! You can see it in your face that you are tired. The Rigors I think the doctor called it, those sound terrifying.. I heard you even chipped a tooth they were so bad. That sounds awful. I'm sorry that you are not able to be with your family. That is hard for anyone and I'm sorry you have to deal with that. I think you are amazing for continuing to do your show from your basement so you can show us what it's really like. I think you are amazing for offering to send people the extra oxygen monitors that you have. I agree with the doctor when he said that you deserve some time off!! As much as I will miss seeing you at night! My prayers are with you Chris. May you feel better soon. Best wishes from Boston. #letsgetafterit #stayhometogether #wewillgetthroughthis #cuomoprimetime
